/*
# [Operation Name]
Add Instructor Column to Classes Table

## Query Description: [This operation adds a new 'instructor' column of type JSONB to the 'classes' table. This column is intended to store instructor details like name and avatar URL. This change is non-destructive and should not affect existing data. It is required to fix an error where the application tries to access this missing column.]

## Metadata:
- Schema-Category: ["Structural"]
- Impact-Level: ["Low"]
- Requires-Backup: [false]
- Reversible: [true]

## Structure Details:
- Table(s) Affected: public.classes
- Column(s) Added: instructor (JSONB)

## Security Implications:
- RLS Status: [Enabled]
- Policy Changes: [No]
- Auth Requirements: [None]

## Performance Impact:
- Indexes: [None]
- Triggers: [None]
- Estimated Impact: [Low. Adding a nullable column is a fast metadata-only change on PostgreSQL.]
*/
-- Add the instructor column to the classes table
ALTER TABLE public.classes
ADD COLUMN instructor JSONB;
-- Add a comment to document the new column's purpose
COMMENT ON COLUMN public.classes.instructor IS 'Stores instructor details, e.g., {"name": "John Doe", "avatarUrl": "..."}';
